==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lying
<hw>Ly"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <def>of
<er>Lie</er>, to tell a falsehood.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lying</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Lying
<hw>Ly"ing</hw>, <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <def>of <er>Lie</er>, to be
supported horizontally.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Lying panel</b></col> <fld>(Arch.)</fld>, <cd>a panel in
which the grain of the wood is horizontal.</cd> <mark>[R.]</mark> --
<col><b>Lying to</b></col> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>, <cd>having the sails so
disposed as to counteract each other.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lying-in</ent>⟦br⟧
